      "learned": "All substances are made of atoms connected by chemical bonds, but different bond types produce different large-scale structures and therefore different physical properties (solubility, conductivity, hardness). Valence electrons — the outermost electrons of atoms — are involved in forming these bonds, and understanding how they behave is the key to explaining the phenomenon.",
